CKNE scales tenants by allocating topic partitions and fetch budgets proportional to CKNE. High CKNE gets more partitions, higher max in-flight messages, and shorter backoff; low CKNE shares are throttled with reduced partitions and longer backoff intervals.

## CKNE-to-Quotas Mapping

```javascript
function computeQuotas(ckne, totalPartitions, baselineSLA) {
  const ckneWeight = Math.max(ckne, 0.1); // floor for baseline
  const partitionQuota = Math.floor(totalPartitions * ckneWeight / totalCKNE);
  const fetchRate = Math.max(baselineSLA, ckne * 1000); // msgs/sec
  const maxInFlight = Math.ceil(ckne * 100);
  const backoffMs = Math.max(100, (1 - ckne) * 5000);

  return { partitionQuota, fetchRate, maxInFlight, backoffMs };
}
```

## Minute-by-Minute Degradation Loop

```javascript
async function degradationLoop(brokerState) {
  const metrics = await collectTelemetry();
  const sortedTenants = metrics.tenants.sort((a, b) => b.ckne - a.ckne);

  // Step 1: Reallocate partitions from low to high CKNE
  for (const tenant of sortedTenants) {
    if (tenant.ckne < 0.3 && tenant.backlog > threshold) {
      const reclaimed = Math.floor(tenant.partitionQuota * 0.5);
      tenant.partitionQuota -= reclaimed;

      // Redistribute to high CKNE tenants
      const highCKNETenants = sortedTenants.filter(t => t.ckne > 0.7);
      highCKNETenants.forEach(t => {
        t.partitionQuota += Math.floor(reclaimed / highCKNETenants.length);
      });
    }
  }

  // Step 2: Apply backpressure
  for (const tenant of sortedTenants) {
    if (tenant.utilization > 0.9) {
      tenant.fetchRate *= 0.8;
      tenant.backoffMs *= 1.5;
    }
  }

  // Step 3: Enforce baseline SLA
  for (const tenant of sortedTenants) {
    tenant.fetchRate = Math.max(tenant.fetchRate, baselineSLA);
    tenant.partitionQuota = Math.max(tenant.partitionQuota, 1);
  }
}
```

## Fairness Guarantees & Preemption Rules

- **Baseline SLA**: Minimum 1 partition and 100 msgs/sec for all tenants
- **Preemption**: Low CKNE (<0.2) tenants can be preempted if backlog > 10k messages
- **Fairness**: No tenant can lose more than 50% of quota in single cycle
- **Recovery**: Preempted tenants get priority when CKNE improves

